        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer167594799" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3249185464227513012">The primary components of traditional fantasy are something like: heroes, honor, dragons, magic, strange lands and journeys. To anyone who reads a lot in this genre, these are so overworked and worn down that you can&apos;t feel anything anymore when you read about them. Everything&apos;s been done before, and it sometimes feels like there&apos;s no new &quot;magic&quot; to be squeezed out of them. But it seems that there very much still is when Gene Wolfe writes about them. This is a powerful and important novel, and I</span>
  <span id="freeText3249185464227513012" style="display:none">The primary components of traditional fantasy are something like: heroes, honor, dragons, magic, strange lands and journeys. To anyone who reads a lot in this genre, these are so overworked and worn down that you can't feel anything anymore when you read about them. Everything's been done before, and it sometimes feels like there's no new "magic" to be squeezed out of them. But it seems that there very much still is when Gene Wolfe writes about them. This is a powerful and important novel, and I think if you could ask them you inner child would very much demand that you read it. And so do I. </span>
