<div id="review_58408837" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/58408837" />
    <a title="Gericke" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2243671-gericke"><img alt="Gericke" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/58408837?book_show_action=true">Jun 04, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gericke" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gericke" href="/user/show/2243671-gericke">Gericke</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780765347015" href="/book/show/60212.The_Knight">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer58408837" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17328434926608022157">I loved this book from start to finish. The writing is done in such a way as to create a completely different feel for the book: It&apos;s written as a letter from a younger brother to his older brother. That being said the writing can be difficult to follow, because he leaves out any unimportant fact (like traveling through the forest when nothing actually happens), and I do suggest reading or at least referring to the character guide in the beginning as that will help cut down on any confusion.<br/><br/>The </span>
  <span id="freeText17328434926608022157" style="display:none">I loved this book from start to finish. The writing is done in such a way as to create a completely different feel for the book: It's written as a letter from a younger brother to his older brother. That being said the writing can be difficult to follow, because he leaves out any unimportant fact (like traveling through the forest when nothing actually happens), and I do suggest reading or at least referring to the character guide in the beginning as that will help cut down on any confusion.<br /><br />The entire book is filled with symbolism that can be extracted to create a much larger and more meaningful experience. It brings out little pieces of truth that we often may not think of until they are presented in a way different from what we are used to receiving elsewhere. I definitely suggest this book and it sequel.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17328434926608022157" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


